# SatTrack — API Rules

## Server Proxies (`server/api/`) — all POST
All endpoints are server-side only: keys never in client bundle, CORS handled, Space-Track auth cookies managed here.

| Proxy file | External API | Purpose | Rate limit |
|---|---|---|---|
| `n2yo.post.ts` | N2YO | Pass predictions + real-time positions | 1000/hr positions, 100/hr passes |
| `space-track.post.ts` | Space-Track | TLE data | — |
| `celestrak.post.ts` | CelesTrak | TLE fallback | — |
| `satnogs.post.ts` | SatNOGS | Transponder frequencies | — |
| `amsat.post.ts` | AMSAT | Amateur frequencies | — |

## Space-Track — CRITICAL
- Endpoint: `/basicspacedata/query/class/gp/NORAD_CAT_ID/{ids}/format/json`
- **NEVER** `tle_latest`, `tle`, `tle_publish` — deprecated, return 404
- Returns: `OBJECT_NAME`, `TLE_LINE1`, `TLE_LINE2`
- Constant: `constants/api.ts` → `API_ENDPOINTS.SPACE_TRACK.TLE`

## N2YO Polar Plot Strategy (rate-limit aware)
1. Fetch full predicted path upfront via `visualpasses` or `radiopasses` (100/hr)
2. Draw dashed arc SVG from prediction data
3. During active pass only: poll positions every 5–10s (1000/hr budget)
4. Cache aggressively — reuse prediction data across components

## API Composables (`composables/api/`)
- `useN2YO.ts` — pass predictions + real-time positions
- `useSpaceTrack.ts` — login + TLE fetch
- `useTLEData.ts` — TLE orchestration: Space-Track first, CelesTrak fallback
- `useSatnogs.ts` — transponder/frequency data
- `useSatelliteSearch.ts` — satellite name/NORAD search

## Constants
- `constants/api.ts` — all endpoints, cache durations (TLE: 2hr, transmitters: 6hr), timeouts
- `constants/satellite.ts` — default tracked satellites, categories
